On October 19, 2009, the White House issued a statement announcing that President Obama had signed several bills into law. The bills included H.R. 1687, which designated a building in Canton, Ohio as the "Ralph Regula Federal Building and United States Courthouse"; H.R. 2053, which designated a courthouse in El Paso, Texas as the "Albert Armendariz, Sr., United States Courthouse"; H.R. 2121, which authorized the General Services Administration to convey the U.S. Custom House to the Galveston Historical Foundation; H.R. 2498, which designated a building in Chicago, Illinois as the "William O. Lipinski Federal Building"; H.R. 2913, which designated a courthouse in Key West, Florida as the "Sidney M. Aronovitz United States Courthouse"; and S. 1289, which established procedures for executing federal court orders in response to requests from foreign authorities for assistance in criminal investigations or prosecutions.